ğŸ“Œ Backend - E-Learning Platform

This repository contains the backend of the E-Learning Platform, developed using Spring Boot and following a monolithic architecture. The backend is responsible for user authentication, course management, quizzes, and certification.

ğŸš€ Features

User Management: Registration, login, JWT authentication, and role-based access (Admin/User).

Course Service: Add, update, view, and delete courses.

Quiz Service: Manage questions, attempt quizzes, and evaluate results.

Certificate Service: Generate certificates for passed quizzes.

Security: JWT-based authentication across all services.

Database: MySQL and MongoDB integration for persistence.

ğŸ—ï¸ Tech Stack

Language: Java 17+

Framework: Spring Boot (REST APIs, Spring Security, JPA)

Databases: MySQL

Authentication: JWT & bcrypt

Build Tool: Maven

Other Tools: Git, Jenkins, Kubernetes (optional for deployment)

âš™ï¸ Setup & Installation

Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/elearning-backend.git
cd elearning-backend


Configure Databases

Update application.properties / application.yml with your MySQL & MongoDB credentials.

Build & Run

mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run

ğŸ”‘ API Endpoints
User Service

POST /api/users/register â†’ Register new user

POST /api/users/login â†’ Login & get JWT token

GET /api/users/me â†’ Get logged-in user profile

Course Service

GET /api/courses â†’ View all courses

POST /api/courses â†’ Add new course (Admin only)

DELETE /api/courses/{id} â†’ Delete course (Admin only)

Quiz Service

GET /api/quizzes/{id} â†’ Fetch quiz

POST /api/quizzes/attempt â†’ Attempt quiz

GET /api/quizzes/result/{id} â†’ Get result

Certificate Service

GET /api/certificates/{userId} â†’ Download certificate

